        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 1:14PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 114 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Lagrange, or 11 miles southwest of Bolivar, moving
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bolivar, Lagrange, Grand Junction, La Grange, Hickory Valley,
Saulsbury, Pattersonville, Van Buren, Middleburg, and Forty Five.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
